props.text: This module will explore the principles and practices of inquiry-based science education. Participants will learn how to design and implement engaging, student-centered science lessons that foster critical thinking, problem-solving, and scientific inquiry skills. The module will delve into strategies for creating authentic learning experiences, using technology effectively, and assessing student learning in a meaningful way.

props.text:
By the end of this module, participants will be able to:

  • Define inquiry-based science education and explain its benefits.
  • Design inquiry-based science lessons aligned with Next Generation Science Standards (NGSS).
  • Implement effective instructional strategies to promote student engagement and critical thinking.
  • Use a variety of assessment tools to measure student learning and progress.
  • Incorporate technology to enhance science learning experiences.
  • Create a supportive classroom culture that fosters scientific inquiry.

props.text:
Throughout this module, consider the following:

  • What is the role of the teacher in inquiry-based science education?
  • How can I design engaging and challenging science investigations?
  • What strategies can I use to promote scientific discourse and collaboration?
  • How can I assess student learning in an inquiry-based classroom?
  • What are the ethical implications of scientific inquiry?

props.text:
To complete the module, you will:

  1. Review: Module 1 Lecture Presentation
  2. Read: Chapter 1 in your textbook
  3. Discuss: Join your classmates in a Group Discussion regarding your current science teaching practices and identify areas for improvement.
  4. Create: Work individually to create a presentation an inquiry-based lesson plan for your next science class, focusing on student-centered learning.
